*.sh eol=lf

# Git LFS — binary motion-capture artifacts under data/ibaraki_radio_taiso/.
# These patterns affect commits made from this point forward. The existing
# binaries in commits 811481d (source zips) and 9e5df89 (converted FBX 7700)
# were committed before LFS was enabled and remain as plain blobs on origin —
# that's a deliberate trade (see docs/fbx3000_intel_handoff.md for context).
#
# Forward-only LFS means anyone cloning fresh will get the past binaries via
# normal git transport (no LFS install required for read-only use) but any
# NEW binaries added under data/ibaraki_radio_taiso/ will go to LFS and
# require `git lfs install` plus LFS bandwidth on push.
data/ibaraki_radio_taiso/**/*.zip filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
data/ibaraki_radio_taiso/**/*.fbx filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
data/ibaraki_radio_taiso/**/*.bvh filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
data/ibaraki_radio_taiso/**/*.npz filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text